name: Bills vs Dolphins
summary: The Buffalo Bills dominated the Miami Dolphins in Thursday Night Football, with a final score of 31-10. The Bills took an early lead and never looked back, cruising to a comfortable victory. Unfortunately, the game was marred by an injury to Dolphins quarterback Tua Tagovailoa, who exited the game in the second quarter with a concussion. The Bills outplayed the Dolphins in all aspects of the game, and the victory is a statement of intent for the Bills as they look to challenge for the AFC East title.

name: Jon Bon Jovi
summary: Musician Jon Bon Jovi was credited with preventing a potential suicide when he helped talk a woman off a pedestrian bridge in Nashville, Tennessee. The incident occurred while Bon Jovi was filming a music video on the bridge. When he noticed the woman standing on the ledge, he approached her and engaged her in conversation. Bon Jovi and others on the scene helped the woman down from the ledge and she was taken to a nearby hospital for evaluation. Police officials praised Bon Jovi's actions, noting that he was instrumental in preventing a tragedy.

name: Edward Caban
summary: In New York City, Mayor Adams has declined to endorse Police Commissioner Edward Caban, who is facing scrutiny under an ongoing investigation. Caban has since resigned, citing a desire to focus solely on the NYPD. The investigation has also uncovered that Caban's twin brother has a checkered past as an ex-cop and is under federal investigation as an alleged "fixer" for NYC hotspots. The NYPD has faced criticism for dismissing hundreds of misconduct cases, including stop-and-frisks, without reviewing them. The federal investigation into the Adams administration has led to the resignation of several officials, including the NYPD commissioner, fueling speculation about the future of the NYPD and the extent of the corruption probe.

name: Friday the 13th
summary: Friday the 13th is considered an unlucky day, with various superstitions surrounding it. The most common superstitions include avoiding crossing paths with a black cat, walking under a ladder, or opening an umbrella indoors. Some people believe that it's a day when bad luck is more likely to strike, while others see it as an opportunity to celebrate or engage in superstitious activities. Despite the negative connotations, certain businesses and organizations capitalize on the occasion, offering special promotions and events related to Friday the 13th. Additionally, some tattoo shops offer special deals on Friday the 13th-themed tattoos.
